    <p>10 June 2025</p>
    <h2 id="next-steps-retiring-10062025" class="govuk-heading-m">Next steps announced in retirement of MoJ Forms </h2>
    <p>MoJ Forms will soon remove the ability to create new forms as part of the ongoing efforts to <a class="govuk-link" href="#migration-update-20082024">retire the platform</a>.</p>
    <p>This will happen in 2 phases:</p>
    <ul>
    <li>From 1 July, the team will remove the option to "Create a new form‚Äù in the editor. Users can continue to work on any forms that are in development after this time.</li>
    <li>From 1 August, the team will stop granting approval for new forms to go live. </li>
    </ul>
    <p>Users will continue to be able to edit and publish updates to live forms as normal.</p>
    <p>The team will also stop granting access to the platform to new users. However, they will continue to support teams that need to transfer ownership of live forms to new users.</p>
    <p>Plans for migrating forms off MoJ Forms are ongoing. Timescales for the migration have been extended into 2026 to allow time for the most complex forms to make alternative arrangements.</p>
