    <p>29 January 2024</p>
    <h2 id="govuk-start-page-29012024" class="govuk-heading-m">New start page option for publishing on GOV.UK</h2>
    <p>You can now choose between 2 types of start page for your forms:</p>
    <ul>
    <li>an MoJ Forms start page - the page you've been using up to now that is created as part of your form</li>
    <li>a GOV.UK start page - which a GOV.UK publisher would create for you on GOV.UK</li>
    </ul>
    <p>With a GOV.UK start page, the page sits on GOV.UK instead of in your form. The regular start page in your form is removed and any links to the start page, such as in your form's header, are updated to point to the GOV.UK URL.</p>
    <p>Learn more about <a class="govuk-link" href="/building-and-editing/#start-page">choosing between the different start page options</a> in the user guide.</p>
